Apple today released <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/macos-sequoia/">macOS Sequoia</a> 15.4.1, a minor update to the &zwnj;macOS Sequoia&zwnj; operating system that launched in September. &zwnj;macOS Sequoia&zwnj; 15.4.1 comes two weeks after the <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/03/31/apple-releases-macos-sequoia-15-4/">launch of macOS Sequoia 15.4</a>.<br/>
<br/>
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-955370" src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2024/06/macOS-Sequoia-Feature.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" /><br/>
Mac users can download the ‌‌&zwnj;macOS Sequoia&zwnj;‌‌ update through the Software Update section of System Settings. It is available for free on all Macs able to run macOS 15.<br/>
<br/>
According to Apple's release notes, ‌&zwnj;macOS Sequoia&zwnj;‌ 15.4.1 includes important bug fixes and security updates, and is recommended for all users.<br/>
